Support these block patterns:

 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `http://127.0.0.1/a`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.protocol&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `http://`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.host&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `127.0.0.1`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.port&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `80`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.d&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `/a`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.i&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `/1`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.path&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `/foo/bar`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.query&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `?foo=bar&baz=qux`
 - <code>&#x5B;<span>&#x5B;url.current&#x5D;</span>&#x5D;</code> → `http://127.0.0.1/a/foo/bar/1?foo=bar&baz=qux`
